TITLE: Activating and Deactivating Identities with Ory SDK in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to use the Ory SDK to change the activation state of user identities. It includes import statements and functions to set an identity as active or inactive, enabling control over whether a user can engage with self-service login flows. The snippet requires the Ory SDK for JavaScript to be installed and properly configured with API credentials. The main parameters include the identity ID and the desired state; it outputs the updated identity state or an error if the operation fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/identities/model/identity-state.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { V0alpha2Api, Configuration } from '@ory/client';

const ory = new V0alpha2Api(new Configuration({
  basePath: 'https://your-ory-server.com',
}));

async function setIdentityState(identityId, activate = true) {
  try {
    const response = await ory.adminUpdateIdentityStatus(identityId, { state: activate ? 'active' : 'inactive' });
    console.log(`Identity ${identityId} is now ${activate ? 'active' : 'inactive'}`);
    return response.data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to update identity state:', error);
    throw error;
  }
}

// Example usage
setIdentityState('identity123', false);
```

