TITLE: Dumping Hydra tables using pg_dump for migration (PostgreSQL)
DESCRIPTION: This command uses pg_dump to export specific tables from a PostgreSQL database. It excludes owner and ACL information, quotes all identifiers, and outputs the data to a file named hydra-dump.sql.  The DSN specifies the database connection string.  The -a flag means dump only the data, not the schema.  The tables dumped are those associated with hydra client and OAuth2 data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/hydra/self-hosted/merge-multiple-db-secrets.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
pg_dump --verbose -a  \
	--format=p \
	--no-owner \
	--no-acl \
	--quote-all-identifiers \
	-t hydra_client \
	-t hydra_oauth2_authentication_session \
	-t hydra_oauth2_authentication_request \
	-t hydra_oauth2_authentication_request_handled \
	-t hydra_oauth2_consent_request \
	-t hydra_oauth2_consent_request_handled \
	-t hydra_oauth2_code \
	-t hydra_oauth2_access \
	-t hydra_oauth2_refresh \
	-f hydra-dump.sql \
	<DSN>
```

