TITLE: Enabling PKCE for OIDC Providers in YAML Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet configures the OIDC method under Ory Identities' self-service settings to enable PKCE. Setting 'pkce' to 'auto' allows Ory to automatically use PKCE if the OIDC provider advertises support. It requires specifying the issuer URL for automatic OIDC configuration. This snippet is used within the identity configuration file before applying changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/social-signin/oidc-pkce.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# ...
selfservice:
  methods:
    oidc:
      enabled: true
      config:
        providers:
          - id: generic
            provider: generic # or another provider
            issuer_url: https://accounts.google.com # must be set to enable automatic configuration
            pkce: auto # default: perform PKCE if the provider advertises support for it
            # ... other configuration options
# ...
```

