TITLE: Activating and Deactivating Identities with Ory SDK in Go
DESCRIPTION: This Go snippet shows how to utilize the Ory SDK to modify user identity states programmatically. It sets up the client configuration and uses the provided method to activate or deactivate an identity by specifying the identity ID and target state. The code requires the Ory Go SDK and proper API server configuration. Inputs are the identity identifier and boolean flag for activation; outputs include the updated identity object or errors for failure conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/identities/model/identity-state.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"context"
	"fmt"
	"log"

	ory "github.com/ory/client-go"
)

func main() {
	client := ory.NewAPIClient(ory.NewConfiguration())
	identityId := "identity123"
	activate := false

	ctx := context.Background()
	update := ory.AdminUpdateIdentityStatusBody{
		State: "inactive",
	}
	if activate {
		update.State = "active"
	}

	identity, resp, err := client.V0alpha2Api.AdminUpdateIdentityStatus(ctx, identityId).AdminUpdateIdentityStatusBody(update).Execute()
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatalf("Failed to update identity state: %v", err)
	}

	fmt.Printf("Identity %s state updated to %s\n", identityId, *identity.State)
	_ = resp
}
```

