TITLE: Requesting OAuth2 Authorization with PKCE in SPA with Redirect in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet constructs an authorization URL for a Single Page Application (SPA) using PKCE, redirecting the user to start the OAuth2 authorization process with secure code challenge parameters. It ensures the client can securely authenticate without exposing secrets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/oauth2-oidc/authorization-code-flow.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
// Request consent
const { codeChallenge, codeVerifier } = await generatePKCES256()
const clientId = "your_client_id"
const authorizationUrl = `https://$PROJECT_SLUG.projects.oryapis.com/oauth2/auth?response_type=code&client_id=${clientId}&redirect_uri=https://myapp.com/callback&scope=openid&state=12345&code_challenge_method=S256&code_challenge=${codeChallenge}`

// Redirect user
window.location = authorizationUrl
```

