TITLE: Checking Permissions with Ory Permissions Python SDK Using Bearer Authentication
DESCRIPTION: A comprehensive example demonstrating how to check permissions for a specific subject using the Ory Permissions Python SDK. It involves setting up a configuration with Bearer token authentication, instantiating the PermissionApi client, and calling the check_permission method with parameters for namespace, object, relation, and subject identifiers. The snippet includes error handling via an exception and prints the permission check result. Dependencies include the ory_client package and Python standard modules like time and pprint.
