DESCRIPTION: This YAML configuration snippet shows how to add schema versioning within Ory by defining multiple schema versions and updating the `default_schema_id`. Existing identities continue to use their original schema, while new ones are created with the updated schema version. URLs point to base64-encoded JSON schema definitions for each version. Dependencies include schema files properly encoded in base64 and referenced in the URL. This approach enables non-disruptive migrations, with schema selection controlled per identity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/manage-identities/35_best-practices.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
identity:
  default_schema_id: user_v1
  schemas:
    - id: user_v0
      url: base64://{b46-encoded-user_v0}
    - id: user_v1
      url: base64://{b46-encoded-user_v1}
```

