TITLE: Mapping SAML Claims to Ory Identity Schema Using Jsonnet
DESCRIPTION: This Jsonnet snippet provides an example of how to map incoming SAML attributes to the Ory identity schema traits. It first imports the 'claims' variable as an external input, representing the claims extracted from a SAML assertion. The code maps the primary email attribute directly and conditionally includes the 'firstName' and 'lastName' attributes if they exist within the raw claims. This approach ensures dynamic handling of optional attributes and enforces correct trait assignment for downstream identity management. Prerequisites include defining the appropriate identity schema and receiving claims objects with nested raw_claims fields from the SAML Identity Provider.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/organizations/organizations.mdx#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: jsonnet
CODE:
```
local claims = std.extVar('claims');

{
  identity: {
    traits: {
      email: claims.email,
      [if std.objectHas(claims, "raw_claims") && std.objectHas(claims.raw_claims, "firstName") then "firstName" else null]: claims.raw_claims.firstName,
      [if std.objectHas(claims, "raw_claims") && std.objectHas(claims.raw_claims, "lastName") then "lastName" else null]: claims.raw_claims.lastName,
    },
  },
}
```

