TITLE: Ory Identities config: VK Provider (YAML)
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet shows how to configure the VKontakte social sign-in provider in the Ory Identities configuration. It includes the provider ID, client ID, client secret, mapper URL (either Base64 encoded or a direct URL), and scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/social-signin/75_vk.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
selfservice:
  methods:
    oidc:
      config:
        providers:
          - id: vk # this is `<provider-id>` in the Authorization callback URL. DO NOT CHANGE IT ONCE SET!
            provider: vk
            client_id: .... # Replace this with the OAuth2 Client ID provided by VK app
            client_secret: .... # Replace this with the OAuth2 Client Secret provided by VK app
            mapper_url: "base64://{YOUR_BASE64_ENCODED_JSONNET_HERE}"
            # Alternatively, use an URL:
            # mapper_url: https://storage.googleapis.com/abc-cde-prd/9cac9717f007808bf17f22ce7f4295c739604b183f05ac4afb4
            scope:
              - email # required for email and email_verified claims in the near future
      enabled: true
```

