TITLE: Configuring Access Rule JWT Authenticator in YAML
DESCRIPTION: Configures the JWT authenticator handler specifically for a single access rule defined in a YAML file. This configuration overrides global settings for this particular rule. It includes specifying the `jwt` handler, JWK Set URLs, scope strategy, required scopes, target audiences, trusted issuers, allowed algorithms, and the location to extract the token from.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/oathkeeper/pipeline/authn.md#_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# Some Access Rule: access-rule-1.yaml
id: access-rule-1
# match: ...
# upstream: ...
authenticators:
  - handler: jwt
    config:
      jwks_urls:
        - https://my-website.com/.well-known/jwks.json
        - https://my-other-website.com/.well-known/jwks.json
        - file://path/to/local/jwks.json
      scope_strategy: none
      required_scope:
        - scope-a
        - scope-b
      target_audience:
        - https://my-service.com/api/users
        - https://my-service.com/api/devices
      trusted_issuers:
        - https://my-issuer.com/
      allowed_algorithms:
        - RS256
      token_from:
        query_parameter: auth-token
        # or
        # header: Custom-Authorization-Header
        # or
        # cookie: auth-token
```

