TITLE: Generating Ory Recovery Link via Admin API (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: This shell command uses `curl` to call the Ory Admin API's `/admin/recovery/link` endpoint to generate a unique recovery link for a specific user identity. It requires an API key for authorization and the `identity_id` of the user created in the previous step. The `expires_in` property sets the link's validity period.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/manage-identities/40_invite-users.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
curl --request POST -sL \
   --header "Authorization: Bearer {ORY_API_KEY}" \
   --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
   --data '{
   "expires_in": "12h",
   "identity_id": "$ACCOUNT_ID"
   }' https://{project-slug}.projects.oryapis.com/admin/recovery/link
```

