TITLE: Complex Matching with Error and Remote IP (YAML)
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet illustrates a complex matching configuration that combines error types and remote IP address matching. It uses `OR` to combine error types and IP addresses within each `when` clause and `AND` to combine `error` and `request` conditions. Specifically, it checks if the error is either `unauthorized` or `internal_server_error` AND the request comes from a specific IP range OR if the error is `forbidden` or `not_found` AND the request has `text/html` or `text/xhtml` in the `Accept` header and `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` or `multipart/form-data` in the `Content-Type` header.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/oathkeeper/pipeline/error.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# .oathkeeper.yaml
errors:
  handlers:
    redirect:
      enabled: true
      config:
        when:
          - error:
              - unauthorized
              # OR
              - internal_server_error

            # AND
            request:
              remote_ip:
                match:
                  - 192.168.1.0/24
                  # OR
                  - 192.178.1.0/24

          # OR
          - error:
              - forbidden
              # OR
              - not_found

            # AND
            request:
              header:
                accept:
                  - text/html
                  # OR
                  - text/xhtml

                # AND
                content_type:
                  - application/x-www-form-urlencoded
                  # OR
                  - multipart/form-data
```

