TITLE: Configuring DingTalk as OIDC Provider - YAML
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet shows how to configure DingTalk as an OIDC provider in the Ory Identities configuration. It includes settings for the client ID, client secret, mapper URL (either Base64 encoded or a direct URL), and scopes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/social-signin/80_dingtalk.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
selfservice:
  methods:
    oidc:
      enabled: true
      config:
        providers:
          - id: dingtalk # this is `<provider-id>` in the Authorization callback URL. DO NOT CHANGE IT ONCE SET!
            provider: dingtalk
            client_id: .... # Replace this with the OAuth2 Client ID provided by DingTalk
            client_secret: .... # Replace this with the OAuth2 Client Secret provided by DingTalk
            mapper_url: "base64://{YOUR_BASE64_ENCODED_JSONNET_HERE}"
            # Alternatively, use an URL:
            # mapper_url: https://storage.googleapis.com/abc-cde-prd/9cac9717f007808bf17f22ce7f4295c739604b183f05ac4afb4
            scope:
              # DingTalk supports only the `openid` or `openid corpid` scopes. For a basic setup, use the `openid` scope.
              - openid
```

