TITLE: Generating RSA Key Pair AWS CloudHSM Bash
DESCRIPTION: Command using the `pkcs11-tool` to generate a new RSA key pair (4096 bits) directly inside the AWS CloudHSM via its PKCS#11 interface. The key is assigned a label and ID, and is marked as private and sensitive.

Dependencies: `pkcs11-tool`, AWS CloudHSM client with PKCS#11 library, valid PIN and token label.

Parameters: `--module` (library path), `--pin`, `--token-label`, `--keypairgen` (action), `--key-type` (algorithm and size), `--label`, `--id`, `--usage-sign`, `--private`, `--sensitive` (flags to prevent export/visibility).
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/hydra/self-hosted/hsm-support.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
pkcs11-tool \
   --module /opt/cloudhsm/lib/libcloudhsm_pkcs11.so \
   --pin <PIN> \
   --token-label <LABEL> \
   --keypairgen \
   --key-type rsa:4096 \
   --label hydra.openid.id-token \
   --id <ID> \
   --login \
   --usage-sign \
   --private \
   --sensitive
```

