TITLE: Social Sign-In Provider Configuration for Discord - YAML
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet illustrates how to define Discord as an OIDC provider within the Ory identity service configuration. It references secrets for client ID and client secret, specifies the location of the data mapping (either as a Base64-encoded string or URL), and declares required OIDC scopes. This configuration must be merged into the broader Ory selfservice identity YAML before deployment.
