TITLE: Defining OpenAPI Request Body Parameters (Go)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to define request parameters, particularly a request body, for an OpenAPI route using `go-swagger` annotations. It uses `swagger:parameters` linked to the operation ID, defines a struct for the parameters (`adminCreateIdentity`), and specifies the body using `in: body` pointing to a separate model (`adminCreateIdentityBody`). The body model itself is defined with `swagger:model` and includes field descriptions, `required` annotations, and JSON tags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/ecosystem/contributing.md#_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// swagger:parameters adminCreateIdentity
// nolint:deadcode,unused
type adminCreateIdentity struct {
  // in: body
  Body adminCreateIdentityBody
}

// swagger:model adminCreateIdentityBody
type adminCreateIdentityBody struct {
  // SchemaID is the ID of the JSON Schema to be used for validating the identity's traits.
  //
  // required: true
  SchemaID string `json:"schema_id"`

  // Traits represent an identity's traits. The identity is able to create, modify, and delete traits
  // in a self-service manner. The input will always be validated against the JSON Schema defined
  // in `schema_url`.
  //
  // required: true
  Traits json.RawMessage `json:"traits"`
}

// swagger:route POST /identities v0alpha1 adminCreateIdentity
```

