TITLE: Configuring 'cookie_session' Authenticator with Path/Query Preservation
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet demonstrates configuring the 'cookie_session' authenticator with `preserve_path` and `preserve_query` set to `true`. This ensures that the path and query from the configured `check_session_url` are used when forwarding the request to the session store, instead of being replaced by the incoming request's path and query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/oathkeeper/pipeline/authn.md#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# Some Access Rule Preserving Path: access-rule-2.yaml
id: access-rule-2
# match: ...
# upstream: ...
authenticators:
  - handler: cookie_session
    config:
      check_session_url: https://session-store-host/check-session
      only:
        - sessionid
      preserve_path: true
      preserve_query: true
```

