TITLE: Creating a User with API-based Registration - Shell
DESCRIPTION: This shell script snippet creates a new user using the Ory Identities API-based registration flow. It generates a unique username and password, calls the registration endpoint, and retrieves the session token for subsequent operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/kratos/self-service/flows/user-settings.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
username=dev+docs.$(date +%s)@ory.sh
password=$(openssl rand -base64 12)

actionUrl=$(curl -s -H "Accept: application/json" \
  'https://playground.projects.oryapis.com/self-service/registration/api' | jq -r '.ui.action')

session=$(curl -s  -X POST -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --data '{ "traits.email": "'$username'", "password": "'$password'", "method": "password" }' \
  "$actionUrl")

sessionToken=$(echo $session | jq -r '.session_token')
echo $sessionToken
```

