TITLE: Configuring Custom Migration Job in Ory Hydra YAML
DESCRIPTION: This YAML snippet demonstrates how to enable and customize a migration job for reverting database changes in Ory Hydra. It should be saved as migrate-down-values.yaml and modifies the customMigrations.jobs section to enable the job with arguments that revert the last applied migration step. This approach requires that the Ory Hydra Helm chart and production environment are already configured, and the database is backed up.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/self-hosted/oel/oauth2/revert-database-migrations.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
hydra:
  customMigrations:
    jobs:
      sql-migration-down:
        enabled: true
        customArgs: ["migrate", "sql", "down", "-e", "-y", "--steps", "1"]

```

