TITLE: Custom redirect URL after login or account creation
DESCRIPTION: Sets a specific URL to which users are redirected after login or account creation, overriding default redirects for better navigation flow during development.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/cli/ory-proxy.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
$ ory proxy --project <project-id-or-slug> \
  --default-redirect-url /welcome \
  http://127.0.0.1:3000 \
  https://ory.example.org
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Running Ory Proxy behind a gateway with publish URL
DESCRIPTION: Configurations for running the proxy behind a gateway, requiring the 'publish-url' parameter to specify public access URL, suitable for development but with limitations on URL paths.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/cli/ory-proxy.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
$ ory proxy --project <project-id-or-slug> \
  http://localhost:3000 \
  https://gateway.local:5000
```

