TITLE: Releasing Ory Software via Bash Script - Shell
DESCRIPTION: This shell snippet provides a standardized approach for triggering a release in Ory projects using a remote release script. It requires setting the 'release_as' variable to an appropriate semver version, then executes the release via bash and a remotely-fetched script. Prerequisites are an internet connection and 'curl' installed. Input parameter defines version bumping (patch, minor, major, or explicit semver string). Output is an automated release process as per project conventions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ory/docs/blob/master/docs/ecosystem/contributing.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: shell
CODE:
```
release_as=v1.2.3
bash <(curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ory/meta/master/scripts/release.sh) $release_as

```

